The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Thursday, February 17, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Midnapore, Feb. 16: Residents of Kadamtala in East Midnapore clashed with the police and set buses on fire in protest against the death of a motorcycle rider who was trying to give a police patrol the slip. 

 He was trying to avoid a police party intercepting riders without helmets and collided with a heavy vehicle. He died on the spot and the pillion rider was admitted in hospital. Police had to resort to lathicharge to disperse the mob and normalise traffic on the Mecheda-Haldia road. 

 Santiniketan: The Swedish government has informed Visva-Bharati it would pay Rs 1.71 lakh to the Swedish Academy for the gold and bronze replicas of Rabindranath Tagore?s stolen Nobel medal. 

 Burdwan: Stung by accusations of stealing a bicycle, 18-year-old Sujal Hazra committed suicide at his house here. Police said Hazra, a motor mechanic, had gone to a two-wheeler shop on Monday night to repair his bicycle. Some people beat him up taking him to be a thief. He could not take the insult. 




